For XP operating system, open the "Printers and Faxes" window; this is accessible through "Printers and Other Hardware" in the "Control Panel." Right click on the desired printer, and select "Sharing" from the context menu. Go to the "Sharing" tab, and select the "Share this printer" radio button. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b9/Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b9/Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/aid1386570-v4-728px-Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For Vista and Windows 7 operating systems, go to the "Network and Sharing Center," available through "Network and Internet" in the "Control Panel." Under "Printer Sharing" select "Turn on Printer Sharing" and then "Apply" or "Save Changes." Go to the "Devices and Printers" panel, available from the "Start Menu," right click the desired printer and select "Printer Properties" from the context menu. Under "Sharing" select "Share this printer. "{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/07/Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/07/Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/aid1386570-v4-728px-Activate-Airprint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Create a folder called "AirPrint. "{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/47/Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid1386570-v4-728px-Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you have a 64-bit machine, put this folder in "C:\ Program Files (x86)." and  If you have a 32-bit machine, put this folder in "C:\ Program Files. "{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f5/Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid1386570-v4-728px-Activate-Airprint-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
